President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Washington and ordered federal aid to help with the wildfires that began on August 13, 2015. The Department of Homeland Security and FEMA will coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. The affected areas include several counties and tribes in Washington. FEMA will provide equipment and resources as needed, with emergency protective measures funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Benigno Bern Ruiz has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area.